Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.25,0:00:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ebata Family Grave 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.59,0:00:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get started already.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Masanori, I'm gonna make you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.74,0:01:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! The Daybreak vs. Blackout \NNagoya Castle Showdown reaches its fourth battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.06,0:01:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Having won twice in a row, \NBlackout advances to the third floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.75,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Here to meet them: \Nthe secret brains of Daybreak!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.14,0:01:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the corpse-controlling \NKing of the Dead, Masanori Iseki!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.12,0:01:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi there!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.34,0:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And opposing him is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.72,0:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Blackout's protector deity!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.88,0:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The flawless guardian \Nwho brings everyone together!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.04,0:01:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear little...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.57,0:01:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomari Seto!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's showtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Aurora Fierce Princess\NRight and Wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomari?\NAurora Fierce Princess\NRight and Wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you rather exhaust \Nyour resources at this point?\NAurora Fierce Princess\NRight and Wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you rather exhaust \Nyour resources at this point?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.91,0:03:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When you play through a serious fight,\N you end up dog-tired, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Which opponent do you most want revenge on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, I'd like to give him \Na liiiittle direct punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.38,0:04:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Being boorish again? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Boar"-ish?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.12,0:04:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're all gonna get bowled over by me, \Nso it doesn't matter who's first. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm "all boar"?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we wind this up super-quick? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.54,0:04:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Wind up as a super boar?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.71,0:04:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, your insult interpretation's \Ngetting kinda strained there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be the one to destroy the embodiment of evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You never left much of an impression \Non me from the start, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you strong, Tomari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hecka strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.49,0:04:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can eat a hecka heap of ramen!\NI'm hecka strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.50,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can eat a hecka heap of ramen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.82,0:04:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No one asked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.07,0:04:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If Tomari's involved, there's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Zakusa?! When did you get here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.64,0:04:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And hang on, where have you been all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.79,0:05:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you before that I'm infiltrating \NDaybreak on a request from a certain person? 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.63,0:05:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been sleuthing around, on Tomari's orders...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.73,0:05:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...to find out just who's pulling the strings \Nbehind the chain of disputes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He is entirely the ringleader.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.43,0:05:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The banner burning, and team wrecking...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...was started at Daybreak by that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and not just at Daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you done this plenty of other times?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your aim in doing so, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.57,0:05:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's awfully harsh, \Ndescribing me as the "ringleader."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.20,0:05:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All I did was tell them how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, I'm like... Prometheus?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless we threaten to do something \Nlike banner-burning, nobody'd get serious, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Without something major at stake...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...people won't get desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:06:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Down, down, in the ocean depths \Nwhere light does not reach, the abyss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.70,0:06:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There, in the mire at the very bottom, \Nis the exact sparkle I wish to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of such a self-centered desire...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.52,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...you made our children cry, \Nand now I'll make sure you regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.52,0:06:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna bowl you over on Zakusa's behalf, too. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, shall we begin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up, Vanguard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.25,0:06:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride! Rancor Chain's skill activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice! This is gonna be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.07,0:06:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn! I ride Kyanite Blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.26,0:06:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being serious here...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.57,0:06:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...so you'd better play for real, or you'll lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I set Galactolus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Only, once you're playing for real, I'm gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.40,0:06:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:06:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride! I call Hendrina!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With its skill, I discard three cards \Nfrom the top of my deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.84,0:07:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All I want to see is when someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...has sunk to the very bottom...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.51,0:07:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,...revealing their true self.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.91,0:07:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,With "only that" as my reason for fighting, \Nno person has been able to stop me thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Just try to deny my existence, \Nand my way of being! 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut your mouth. You'll bite your tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.27,0:07:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride Risatt Pink! Its skill activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.10,0:07:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I imprison one card from my opponent's hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.26,0:07:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, with Chevalstud's skill, \NI imprison Hendrina!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.25,0:07:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:08:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Galaxy Central Prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I call Perio Turquoise! Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.67,0:08:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With no air, and no warmth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a fun, fun theme park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.88,0:08:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,While in your cell, you'd better repent!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.03,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.62,0:08:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Perio Turquoise weakens cards \Nthat have left prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.27,0:08:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fighting dirty, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.37,0:08:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really one to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure do get me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride Mysterious Rain Spiritualist, Zorga.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.96,0:08:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Soul Blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,People try to lock away their true nature \Ninside a jail cell called "rationality."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.85,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I call my imprisoned Hendrina.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.37,0:09:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With its skill, I discard three cards \Nfrom the top of my deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.92,0:09:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear. That went poorly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.65,0:09:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't get the card you'd hoped for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.99,0:09:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.37,0:09:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To use its other skill, I retire Hendrina.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.67,0:09:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That removes the need to pay \Na Soul Blast cost for an Alchemagic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.56,0:09:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite an interesting unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets even more interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.27,0:09:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I use Cursed Souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.35,0:09:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And stir in the Spiritual Body Condensation \Nfrom my Drop, using Alchemagic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Alchemagic... allows you to use \Npowerful Order effects in combination?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With Cursed Soul's effect, I call two cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.74,0:09:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Spiritual Body Condensation's effect,\N I call from the Drop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.32,0:09:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The skill of the Roaming Prison Dragon \Nin my Drop
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.99,0:09:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,allows it to be called after using an Order!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's more! Since I used Alchemagic, \Nit gets +10,000 power and an extra critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.01,0:09:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?!\NAnd there's more! Since I used Alchemagic, \Nit gets +10,000 power and an extra critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.84,0:09:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, with Zorga's skill, \NI call from the Drop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.85,0:10:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha-wha-wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.64,0:10:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh... so beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You've filled your entire field \Nwhile hardly using your hand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This deck is unbound \Nby even the concept of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.88,0:10:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.21,0:10:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Twin drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.92,0:10:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess even someone like you \Nhasn't been deserted by God?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is luck, whether good or bad, \Nsomething one should rely on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no belief in luck, much less God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.29,0:10:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if God did exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...wouldn't God's favorite be a kid like Yu-yu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.39,0:10:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's a good and honest kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.44,0:10:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's locked himself up in a teeny cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.76,0:10:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tohya's the opposite: unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.97,0:10:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A wild child who can't \Nremain obediently inside a cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you sent Tohya after Blackout!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.29,0:11:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a spark to ignite something, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's a banner... or a soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard and intercept!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew something must be done about you, \Nor else these battles will never end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! My fighting spirit's replenished!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.71,0:11:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! It really is boring \Nunless I'm enjoying myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.96,0:11:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming up next: \NTomari's Great Criminal Investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The curtain will rise on a lovely arrest drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent, excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.86,0:13:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your willy-nilly calls, \Nthe field's full of perps!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.19,0:13:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to flex my skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride Aurora Battle Princess, Seraph Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Its skill activates! I imprison two rear-guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.13,0:13:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I call Agra Luge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.91,0:13:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,With its skill, I imprison a rear-guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.31,0:13:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I call another Agra Luge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.52,0:13:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With its skill, I imprison a rear-guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.44,0:13:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Chevalstud's skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.51,0:13:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I send the last one...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.64,0:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,...to prison!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your rear-guards have all \Nbeen tossed in the slammer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.82,0:13:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How lenient of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.48,0:13:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, however many petty underlings \Nyou nab, it means nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to take out the boss \Nof the evil organization, y'know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the advice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.15,0:13:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My seriousness is at 100%! \NAnd Seraph Snow's in tip-top shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, it can even achieve a triple drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.59,0:13:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I call Suppress Gleamer! Its skill activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.77,0:14:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When there are at least three imprisoned, \NI can call one more Suppress Gleamer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.22,0:14:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now my seriousness is at 200%!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.84,0:14:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.47,0:14:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.73,0:14:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seraph Snow attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.78,0:14:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Triple drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.12,0:14:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You assume a lack of jail cells \Nmeans freedom, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.11,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Glorifying freedom for selfish reasons \Nis just displaying selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.25,0:14:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Robbing other people of their freedom... \Nis the one freedom nobody would allow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.90,0:14:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Draw trigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Your rational argument's boring!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.39,0:14:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.67,0:14:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.35,0:14:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm... yeah, you're way stronger than I assumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, however many times \NI get tossed in a cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.54,0:14:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna keep surging my way out \Nagain and again, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:15:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll keep tossing you back in \Nhowever many times it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you to the ends of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.97,0:15:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't end until one of us is dead, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.65,0:15:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She's engaging him seriously, \Ntrying to comprehend him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.84,0:15:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomari's always like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.95,0:15:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time... he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.00,0:15:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...he of all people is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.66,0:15:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.10,0:15:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we be hearing it right about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The melody... of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn. Persona ride!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.07,0:15:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With Zorga's skill,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.11,0:15:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I call Hendrina from the Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,With its skill, I discard three cards \Nfrom the top of my deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww, I didn't get it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you do this to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I dig this deep into the deck, \Nyet you're not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.15,0:16:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief, Despair, and Rejection. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure did get rejected!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.74,0:16:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't go the way you're expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.29,0:16:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what makes it fun, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,An excuse for being out of luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.59,0:16:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you before, \Ntalking about stuff like luck or fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.89,0:16:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...is insolent. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.94,0:16:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, while Grief and Despair \Nhaven't bothered to show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.76,0:16:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,neither will that one. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.48,0:16:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,By retiring Hendrina, I remove \Nthe Soul Blast while using Alchemagic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.58,0:16:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the world... will turn inside out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I use Ye Wandering Souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.15,0:16:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And stir in the Spiritual Body Condensation \Nfrom my Drop...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.76,0:16:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...using Alchemagic! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.61,0:16:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Zorga gets an extra drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.93,0:16:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and calls Rancor Chain from the Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.29,0:16:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With the skill of the two \NRoaming Prison Dragons in my Drop,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.14,0:16:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they get called from Drop after I use an Order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.18,0:16:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, if I use Alchemagic, \Nthey get +10,000 power and an extra critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:16:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Counterblast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.30,0:17:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I call the two imprisoned Sea Breeze Abductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is... getting...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally hear it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The melody of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.16,0:17:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's when the real nightmare begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.69,0:17:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Zorga attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard and intercept!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we start chipping away at each other's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, aren't you having fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At this moment, with this stinging, I am now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...fully alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.37,0:18:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Triple drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.11,0:18:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, fill it up! Fill up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.83,0:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...my sake cup!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.35,0:18:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At this late hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.98,0:18:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All that pours out is hell's resentment... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.63,0:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Swallowing up both the dead and the living... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.73,0:18:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of the living becomes \Npandemonium's haunts of wicked men. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.83,0:18:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Over Trigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.37,0:18:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My Vanguard gets +100,000,000 power, \Nand an extra critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...goes through...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.57,0:18:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, my front row gets +10,000 power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.78,0:18:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I draw one card, and heal one damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.93,0:18:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The monstrous rain becomes a storm, \Nmowing down everything in its path! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.54,0:19:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As thanks for throwing me into prison, \NI'll give you these words:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.99,0:19:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Welcome to Hell!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you look at that, she survived it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Work harder, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.64,0:19:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.80,0:19:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.17,0:19:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it! \NYou've still got life to spare, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can keep playing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.41,0:19:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are quite good at this, Tomari!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.60,0:19:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You bore up through all that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.01,0:19:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn't the process left you rather discouraged?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.08,0:19:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.76,0:19:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the face of absolute defeat, \Nhow will you make a reversal? 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.68,0:19:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got something to show, \Nthen by all means, show it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.94,0:19:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock through anything and everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.81,0:20:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock through the "what lies beyond" \Nthat I don't know about!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no absolutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a chance at a reversal. \NThat's how Cardfights are!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, what do you have left, Tomari?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have the intention of winning!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.34,0:20:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.09,0:20:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Just shut up and watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.94,0:20:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Tomari Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The coolest woman in the galaxy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.48,0:20:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand and draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I ride Aurora Fierce Princess, Seraph Purelight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.94,0:20:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Grade 4?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.85,0:20:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You had... a secret ace?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.77,0:20:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the great round-up begins!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,With Seraph Purelight's skill, \NI imprison two apiece
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.59,0:20:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from your hand, your Soul, and your rear-guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.78,0:20:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That many?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.54,0:20:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Chevalstud's skill, I imprison \None rear-guard, and draw one card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.55,0:21:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I call Lourus Yellow and Treuse Green!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sending out triggers?! \NNow that's desperation!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.06,0:21:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?! I've been serious \Nabout this from the beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Seraph Purelight's skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.56,0:21:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For every two cards imprisoned, \Nthe front row units get +5000 power!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.02,0:21:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Since there are eleven imprisoned, \Nthat's +25,000 power!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.40,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, because there are at least ten imprisoned, \Nthe front row units get an extra critical!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.94,0:21:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What? That's entertaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.88,0:21:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,By knowing your opponent, \Nyou won't give in to your hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.63,0:21:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring even more on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all you've got in reserve?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, don't expect me to forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.38,0:21:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let me experience \Nwhat lies beyond an earnest battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.05,0:21:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Going all-out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.13,0:21:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Tomari Seto's spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.10,0:21:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Seraph Purelight attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.29,0:21:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.84,0:21:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Triple drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.85,0:21:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,First check!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.02,0:21:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not enough to hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.68,0:22:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not done yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.34,0:22:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Second check!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.84,0:22:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That fist doesn't look like it's moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.52,0:22:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Third check!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.34,0:22:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Front trigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.54,0:22:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.24,0:22:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My front row units get +10,000 power!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That still won't defeat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.08,0:22:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lourus Yellow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.47,0:22:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...attacks your Vanguard!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.09,0:22:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A victory by the skin of my teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.32,0:22:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.86,0:22:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The iron hammer of justice \Non the depraved monk! 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You have lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.33,0:23:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've succeeded in \Nslightly comprehending the person you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.65,0:23:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take the liberty of saying this once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.87,0:23:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse to forgive a jerk like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.90,0:23:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stop you over and over again, \Nhowever many times it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.03,0:23:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.93,0:23:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll always be someone there \Nto stand in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.21,0:23:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, they'll defeat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.69,0:23:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I feel kinda...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.61,0:23:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your hard work, Tomari.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.55,0:23:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me handle the rest here. \NYou guys hurry on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.58,0:23:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Take good care of Tomari!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.80,0:23:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do, Zakusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.07,0:23:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it... you wanted to say to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.22,0:23:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That... doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.57,0:23:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is Danji, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.46,0:24:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.07,0:24:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.54,0:24:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's strong, fighting with everything on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.21,0:24:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was concerned when he started \Nthe whole "kind older brother" thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.75,0:24:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...but now, he's safely become \Nthe monster he used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.40,0:24:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.43,0:24:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...no...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.01,0:24:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.97,0:24:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,People say...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.20,0:24:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...that holding out an umbrella is kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.17,0:24:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.52,0:24:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.83,0:24:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...in your case...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.42,0:25:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.51,0:25:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Check Out My Card!\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.22,0:25:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.69,0:25:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen!\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.85,0:25:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All you ladies and gentlemen, who youth it up \Nwith cards, and make life-or-death pacts with 'em,\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.49,0:25:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's time to party!\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.22,0:26:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, you get an introduction to \NAurora Fierce Princess, Seraph Purelight!\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.73,0:26:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When you ride it, you arrest two cards each \Nfrom the opponent's hand, rear-guard, and Soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.34,0:26:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not all! For every two cards imprisoned, \Nyour front row units get +5000 power,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.16,0:26:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they also get an extra critical \Nif there are at least ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.03,0:26:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A Piece of Soul\Nand they also get an extra critical \Nif there are at least ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.52,0:26:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of power! Amazing!\NA Piece of Soul
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.49,0:26:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of power! Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.16,0:26:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To Be Continued 
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.37,0:26:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Next Episode 
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.13,0:26:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastion vs Bruce\NResolve 
